        "title": "feat: add per-agent compaction overrides (AI-assisted)",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add agent-scoped compaction and context-pruning overrides so per-agent config can diverge from global defaults.\n- Thread the active agent through CLI compaction and embedded compaction/runtime selection so the correct agent scope is honored.\n- Update the dependent docs and adjacent QA/Telegram/XAI surfaces so the new config shape is documented and exercised.\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n- Closes #52732\n- Related #52751\n- Related #69988\n- Related #19501, #15826, #43834, #6571, #6572, #30452, #57901, #58077, #59863, #60512, #80784, #82008\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior or issue addressed: agent-scoped compaction/context-pruning resolution now honors per-agent overrides instead of only global defaults.\n- Real environment tested: checked-out `feat/agent-compaction-overrides` branch in the local OpenClaw repo.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `corepack pnpm exec tsx /tmp/openclaw-real-behavior-proof.ts`\n- After-fix terminal capture:\n```json\n{\n  \"mergedCompaction\": {\n    \"mode\": \"default\",\n    \"reserveTokensFloor\": 24000,\n    \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\"\n  },\n  \"mergedContextPruning\": {\n    \"mode\": \"cache-ttl\",\n    \"minPrunableToolChars\": 8192,\n    \"ttl\": \"15m\"\n  },\n  \"effectiveTarget\": {\n    \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n    \"model\": \"claude-opus-4-6\"\n  },\n  \"runtimeContext\": {\n    \"workspaceDir\": \"/tmp/workspace\",\n    \"agentDir\": \"/tmp/agent\",\n    \"config\": {\n      \"agents\": {\n        \"defaults\": {\n          \"compaction\": {\n            \"model\": \"gpt-4o\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"list\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"worker\",\n            \"compaction\": {\n              \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-opus-4-6\"\n            }\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n    \"model\": \"claude-opus-4-6\"\n  }\n}\n```\n- Evidence after fix: mergedCompaction kept the default mode and applied the per-agent reserve floor; mergedContextPruning applied cache-ttl plus the agent override; effectiveTarget resolved to anthropic/claude-opus-4-6; runtimeContext matched that resolved target.\n- Observed result after fix: the agent override preserved the default compaction mode while overriding the token floor and context-pruning mode, and the runtime target switched to the agent-specific compaction model.\n- What was not tested: full CI, browser-based flows, and live gateway sessions.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n- Coverage level that should have caught this: unit test, seam/integration test, end-to-end test, and existing coverage already sufficient.\n- Target test or file: src/agents/agent-scope.test.ts, src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/compaction-runtime-context.test.ts, src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts, src/agents/pi-settings.test.ts.\n- Scenario the test should lock in: per-agent compaction/context-pruning merge, per-agent compaction model override, and runtime target selection all remain tied to the resolved agent scope.\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: it covers the config merge point and the runtime consumer, which are the only places this change can drift.\n\n## Security Impact\n- New permissions/capabilities? No\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? No\n- New/changed network calls? No\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? No\n- Data access scope changed? No\n\n## Human Verification\n- Verified scenarios: agent-scoped compaction/context-pruning merge; per-agent compaction target resolution.\n- Edge cases checked: default compaction fields preserved when only some agent fields are overridden.\n- What I did not verify: full CI, browser flows, and live gateway sessions.\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n- Risk: agent-scoped config could diverge from existing default behavior in unexpected ways.\n  - Mitigation: defaults still apply, the merge is explicit, and the resolution path is covered by focused tests and runtime proof.\n",
